# OSS quality

## Before merging

- [ ] `pnpm lint` passes
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
- [ ] `pnpm test` passes
- [ ] New behavior has tests (especially scan rules and WriteGuard)
- [ ] No user memory content in logs, fixtures use synthetic data only

## Public surface

- Exported types and APIs must be documented in JSDoc or README
- Breaking changes need a note in PR description
- Dependencies: prefer small, maintained packages; justify new deps in PR

## Contributor docs

- `CONTRIBUTING.md` — how to run, test, open PR
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — public architecture overview

## License

MIT for OSS core. Third-party licenses respected in NOTICE if needed.

## Release checklist (M5+)

- Version bump in `package.json`
- CHANGELOG entry
- README quickstart verified on clean macOS install
- No secrets or real user paths in repo
